ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was a literature course with an emphasis on cultural history. I would definitely recommend it if students like approaching literature from that perspective.

I would recommed it for those interested in taking a real slice of the Victorian period and studying it in depth. One particularly interested in a cultural approach to studying English would greatly enjoy this course, and for others, it would give a perfect example of how combining texts with context can provide a richer understanding thereof.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Made me reconsider my area because I enjoyed class so much.
I think it helped me have a deeper understanding of this historical period.
